"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"![](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/WZz_VIJRrA4c8E2m7n0Ue.png?height=810&width=2324)\\n\\nHedge.wtf dedicated to building decentralized finance (DeFi) infrastructures for NFTs.   fungible token like erc20s, have many tools at their disposal. However, NFTs like Erc721 is lack financial tools for price discovery and liquidity. The  hedge.wft contract is the first tool we are launching to solve such problems.\\n\\nHedge.\\n\\nwtf smart contract is is an agreement to purchase or sell an NFT at a set price on a future date.\\n\\nIt is a derivative that refers to the underlying asset executed on a future date. You can use a Hedge.wtf smart contract to hedge or speculate, though its non-standardized feature makes it more ideal for hedging.\\n\\nTo minimize price fluctuation, Hedge.wtf smart contract can be applied to lock up a predetermined price. The buyer takes a long position, and the seller takes a short position. The buyer benefits when the price of the underlying asset appreciates, and the inverse is true.\\n\\n**The Use of the** *Hedge.wtf smart contract*\\n\\n**Hedging the Risk of Holding Assets**\\n\\nThe  *Hedge.wtf smart contract*  can be used as a hedging strategy to protect against the risk of holding assets. No matter how confident you are about your investment, there's always some degree of uncertainty, especially in the volatile crypto world. The  *Hedge.wtf smart contract* protects against this risk by allowing traders to enter and agree on future prices of any underlying assets. This way, they never have to worry about what might happen if the market prices move unfavorably during the settlement period\\n\\n**2.2 Locking Up Profits**\\n\\nWith the  *Hedge.wtf smart contract*, cryptocurrency investors can lock up their profits for safekeeping. Short-term investors can lock up their profits to minimize risk and generate income, while long-term investors can do so to maintain their portfolio balances.\\n\\nFollow 